aa(lp72
VNow, this is the part of the talk
p73
aVwhere you may expect me to launch into my plea
p74
aVfor us to all save the coral reefs.
p75
aVBut I have a confession to make:
p76
aVthat phrase drives me nuts.
p77
aVWhether I see it in a tweet, in a news headline
p78
aVor the glossy pages of a conservation brochure,
p79
aVthat phrase bothers me,
p80
aVbecause we as conservationists have been sounding the alarms
p81
aVabout the death of coral reefs for decades.
p82
aVAnd yet, almost everyone I meet, no matter how educated,
p83
aVis not sure what a coral is or where they come from.
p84
aVHow would we get someone to care about the world's coral reefs
p85
aVwhen it's an abstract thing they can barely understand?
p86
aVIf they don't understand what a coral is or where it comes from,
p87
aVor how funny or interesting or beautiful it is,
p88
aVwhy would we expect them to care about saving them?
